# Momus Core Standards

Bug Budget module rebuild. PRD: `prd.md`. Plan: `plan.md`. Full conventions: `conventions.md`.

**Stack:** TypeScript, Next.js 15, Supabase, Inngest, Turborepo, Vitest.

## Architecture

- `packages/domain` — pure business logic, NO framework/DB imports
- `packages/infra` — Supabase, Jira, cache, crypto
- `packages/jobs` — Inngest background jobs
- `apps/web` — Next.js UI + API routes (Vercel)

## Dependency Rule

`domain` → only `shared`. Never import `infra`, `web`, or React from domain.

## Key Constraints

- Behavioral parity with legacy QARATMS (PRD v1.1)
- `bug_budget` table contract must not drift (BB-DATA-07)
- Jira integration is read-only
- Timezone: Asia/Jakarta
- Golden fixtures (Appendix A) are normative tests
